7 An Act relating to property; requiring the retention
of certain documents; requiring accessibility to
8 certain documents; providing time frame to provide
documents to certain parties; requiring notification
9 to homeowners of adoption of an update of a covenant,
condition, or restriction by an owners association;
10 providing for disclosing of certain fees; limiting
fee amounts; prohibiting fee for certain document;
11 providing that a title insurance company shall
include a letter from the owners association to the
12 property owner, at cost to the title insurance
company, which declares the property in good
13 standing; providing for fees of good standing
documents; providing certain disclosure document to
14 be provided by certain parties upon a title
commitment; providing fee for providing certain
15 disclosure documents; providing that a buyer has a
certain time to withdraw from a contract for sale;
16 prohibiting the restrictive covenants which limit the
fair economic use of a property; requiring an owners
17 association to issue to a title company a letter
stating that a homeowner is in good standing;
18 requiring the disclosure by certain parties of the
fee structure surrounding operation of an owners
19 association and any potential charges to homeowner;
requiring the disclosure by certain parties of the
20 fines for violations of the homeowners association's
covenants, conditions, and restrictions; limiting how
21 many times a fine structure may be updated; requiring
certain notification of certain meeting; amending 60
22 O.S. 2021, Section 857, which relates to copies of
recorded covenants and restrictions; modifying
23 terminology; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
